additional.message_body:
So the cards that we have been using this whole time have the contributed amount every week right? I thought they were contributed to a different card, that's why I have been asking for new cards. But if it is the cards that we are having then it should be good!


Thank you for your clarification again. 


Best,
You won’t get new cards until those expire. There should be an expiration date on them. Until then, all money that is being contributed is being added to your cards weekly.

Hi Mrs Carroll,


They are. So when these cards are out of money, we will be shipped the new cards with the new contributed amount in?
Then they should still be good.

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


We all have those 3 cards right now.


Best,

Hi Mrs. Carroll,

 

I'm contacting you on behalf of my dad [personal_name] about the new insurance reapplication for this year. Some hospital called me and said our insurance expired, so I don't know if he had had a new ID number for the insurance or anything to verify that our insurance has been renewed. Can you help with this, please?

 

Thank you and have a great day. 

Best Regards,

They can only mail them to the address on file. Before they cancel these cards, would you check to see if you have any of these. Below are the last 4 digits of the cards that are currently active for each of  you. Please let me know if you have any of these, so they are not cancelled.

Thx

 

[personal_name] last 4 numbers [account_info]

[personal_name] last 4 numbers [account_info]

[personal_name] last 4 numbers [account_info]

Yes sure.


It is [address]. This is the main address that we have been using.


If it is okay, I would like to request 2 cards sent to that address for my parents, and 1 card sent to the address: [address] for me. If it is not possible, please go ahead with sending 3 cards to the [address] address.


Thank you very much!


Best,
Can you verify the address the card should be mailed to and I will check with Sterling?

---
Hi Mrs. Carroll,


I hope you are doing well. I'm writing regarding your email you sent me about the new cards my dad should have received to spend the money on the [health_medical] medical plan. I have been trying to call their customer service's numbers but it's very hard to reach out to them. I was put on hold for more than 30 minutes every time I called them. Do you know if there is another way I can have these cards sent to us? As our old [account_info] benefit cards' balance is running low, it would be great if we can have access to the new cards as soon as possible.


Thank you for your help again, Mrs. Carroll.


Best,

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


Thank you so much! I appreciate your fast assistance always for my family! Have a good day!


Best,
Oh, yes..this is much better. It will be effective on next week’s check.

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


Yes I can. Sorry about that! I attached it below. Thank you for your help!

Hello Hailey,

Are you able to send this document as an attachment rather than in the body of the email so it will print better and not look like a picture?

Thank you,
Carroll

Yes, he should have rec’d a new medical card. Our medical coverage changed to [health_medical] effective 11/1/23. If he did not receive it, he will need to call them to have a new card mailed. If his address is not correct, you will need to send new address to me to update it.

[pii] is [phone_number]


Thank you.

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


I hope you have had a good day. 


I’m contacting today regards of my dad’s paycheck. We would like to have [financial_data] deducted extra from each paycheck according to this form as he has filled in. 
Is this something that I can process through you?


Thank you for your help!


Best,

The card you have may still be good. They usually roll over year to year and don’t expire until the expiration date shown on them. If you want to check, just call Sterling and they can verify the card number that is active.

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


Thank you for your clarification! So the cards that we have been using this whole time don't have this new amount right? It has to be on the new card that he is having right now. I can double-check with him again, and let you know if I still have any questions!


Thank you so much for your response I appreciate it!!!
Best,

Yes, that is correct. Your father is on the [health_medical] medical plan. Airco contributes [financial_data] per year into his [account_info] account. He receives this in a weekly contribution amt of [financial_data] per week. He should have a [account_info] card that he can use to spend this money. If not, you should call [organization_name] (the [account_info] provider) to request a new card mailed. PH# is [phone_number].

Let me know if you have any other questions.

Carroll

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


I hope you are doing well! If you don't mind replying to me, I still have some concerns about my dad's health benefits.


In the last email, you told me that he hadn't updated the HSA deduction, so it was canceled. He told me that for this [organization_name] health insurance, he gets an amount of [account_info] for [financial_data]. Is that true and what is it about? I just need clarification. I know that my dad did not understand English very well so that's why I always have to go back and forth like this with you, I'm so sorry about that. As my family still needs to pay some medical bills I just want to make sure about this problem again!


I'm looking forward to hearing from you. Have a great day!


Best,

Dear Mrs. Carroll,

 

I have called them and have them send us new cards. Thank you so much for your help again.

 

I have one more question, for the [account_info] account, we are not going to do it anymore right, I don't see that in my Dad's account, or is it because we haven't set that up? If I want to set it up, will I have to call the same phone number as well? And for the old [account_info], will the money expire, and if we continue to contribute to the [account_info], will it be contributed in the same account or a new one?

 

Best regards,

If there is no [account_info] deduction on his check, that means he did not update it during open enrollment so it was cancelled. Any money you previously had in the account is still available.

Thank you.

Dear Mrs. Carroll,


I have called them and have them send us new cards. Thank you so much for your help again.


I have one more question, for the [account_info] account, we are not going to do it anymore right, I don't see that in my Dad's account, or is it because we haven't set that up? If I want to set it up, will I have to call the same phone number as well? And for the old [account_info], will the money expire, and if we continue to contribute to the [account_info], will it be contributed in the same account or a new one?


Best regards,

Best Regards,

Dear Mrs. Carroll,

 

Thank you for your help. The address for sending the medical cards is 

[personal_name]

[address]

 

Does that mean I need to contact this phone number [phone_number] to have it sent to our address?

 

Thank you for your help again.

 

Best regards,

Yes. You need to call that number to have [organization_name] send a new card.

Thx

Thank you for your help. The address for sending the medical cards is 
[personal_name]
[address]
